Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.36,0:35:38.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁让你干的\NFor who?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.50,0:35:51.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在可不是保持沉默的时候\NNow is not the time to not say.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.64,0:35:57.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,悄悄话\NWhispers.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.02,0:35:59.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,另一个悄悄话\NThe other Whispers.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.72,0:36:05.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道典范布品服务公司的老板是谁吗\NYou know who owns the Cadillac Linen Service?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.07,0:36:09.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,做洗衣行业的犹太人\NSome Jews in the laundry business.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.02,0:36:11.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-雇主是这么说的  -他们只占部分股份\N- That's what they told me. - They own a part of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.01,0:36:13.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有人是老板\NSomebody else got an interest in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.93,0:36:15.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你知道是谁吗  -不\N- You know who? - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.32,0:36:16.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也可以理解为"是我"
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.32,0:36:16.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道\NI do.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.78,0:36:19.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-是谁  -不  是我\N- Who? - No. I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.66,0:36:21.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其他的股份是我的\NI own the other part.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.13,0:36:23.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而不是我认识持有剩余股份的人\NNot I know somebody who owns the other part.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.85,0:36:30.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,安吉洛  我不知道你有这家公司的股份\NAngelo, I didn't know you had any part of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.63,0:36:32.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要是知道的话\NI would never have done what I did
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.42,0:36:34.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是绝对不会那么做的  我不知道\Nif I knew you were involved. I didn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.29,0:36:36.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我绝不会对你做这种事\NI would never, never do that against you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.80,0:36:38.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,悄悄话没说老板是犹太黑帮吗\NWhispers didn't tell you it was Jew mob?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.50,0:36:40.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有  他说是犹太洗衣妇\NNo, he said Jew washerwomen.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.49,0:36:44.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,犹太洗衣妇\NJew washerwomen.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.35,0:36:47.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他还说了什么\NWhat else he say?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.42,0:36:50.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我猜他让你保密\NI bet he said keep it to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.57,0:36:52.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别跟城里其他人透露一个字\NDon't say nothing to nobody Downtown.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.90,0:36:56.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,的确\NHe did.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.59,0:37:03.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没核实\NI didn't check.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.35,0:37:05.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对不起  我应该先核实一下的\NI'm sorry. I should've checked.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.11,0:37:08.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我能把钱退给他吗  -他用不着了\N- Can I give him his money back? - He won't need it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.77,0:37:09.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你留着吧\NYou can keep it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.24,0:37:11.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不想惹麻烦\NI... I don't want no trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.41,0:37:13.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我把钱退给他吧  我没关系\NI'll just give it back to him and I'm okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.67,0:37:15.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他用不着了\NHe won't need it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.37,0:37:21.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧  谢谢\NOkay. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.85,0:37:22.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢罗素吧\NThank Russell.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.77,0:37:24.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我本来不想浪费时间\NI wouldn't have wasted my time.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.83,0:37:26.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,打算让犹太黑帮找你算账\NI'd have let the Jew mob have you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.82,0:37:31.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你这个朋友真没得说\NYou got a good friend here.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.94,0:37:33.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不知道他多仗义\NYou don't know how good a friend you got.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.88,0:37:36.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我知道  -不  你不知道\N- I... I know. - No, you don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.76,0:37:42.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去吧台那等着吧\NWait by the bar, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.87,0:38:00.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,像这种情况\NIn a case like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.35,0:38:03.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最好的办法就是用全新的家伙\Nthe best thing to do is you use something brand new.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.75,0:38:05.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,刚开箱的\NRight out of the box.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.22,0:38:07.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,否则  你不知道它在哪里被用过\NOtherwise, you don't know where it's been.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.27,0:38:09.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或被谁用过\NYou don't know who's used it,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.09,0:38:11.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跟什么案子有关联\Nwhat crime it was connected to.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.44,0:38:12.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那无异于找死\NThat's suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.10,0:38:16.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以我推荐用全新的  刚开箱的\NSo I recommend something new, straight out of the... the box.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.20,0:38:19.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,冰冷  干净\NStone cold. Clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.91,0:38:23.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你来了\NThere you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.81,0:38:25.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道你会从哪边过来\NI didn't know which way you were coming from.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.82,0:38:27.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道你从哪边...\NI didn't know which way you were...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.32,0:38:35.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然  下一步就是\NNaturally, the next thing you wanna do
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.79,0:38:38.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把家伙扔掉  你得毁灭证据\Nis throw the thing away. You wanna get rid of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.39,0:38:43.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大家都扔在斯古吉尔河的一个地方\NThere's a spot in the Schuylkill River everybody uses.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.73,0:38:45.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果派人潜到河底\NIf they ever send divers down there,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.98,0:38:48.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,找到的武器够武装一个小国家了\Nthey'd be able to arm a small country.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.88,0:38:57.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一名男子在人行道上被枪杀
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.73,0:39:15.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对我来说  杀死悄悄话后  一切都变了\NFor me, everything changed after Whispers.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.06,0:39:21.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就像在军队\NIt was like the army.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.85,0:39:24.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你服从命令\NYou followed orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.52,0:39:27.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听吩咐做事\NYou did the right thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.58,0:39:29.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就会得到相应的奖赏\NYou got rewarded.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.64,0:39:32.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗马别墅餐厅酒吧
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.64,0:39:34.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我替罗素做事\NAnd when I handled things for Russell,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.60,0:39:36.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从来都不是为钱\Nit was never for money,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.05,0:39:37.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是为了表达尊重\Nbut as a show of respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.11,0:39:40.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你给他跑跑腿  帮帮忙\NWhen you ran a little errand, you did a little favor,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.75,0:39:43.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当你需要帮忙的时候  他也还你人情\Nyou got a little favor back if you ever needed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.63,0:39:45.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你总是会需要帮忙的\NAnd you always hurried back.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.69,0:39:46.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-菲尔  你好啊  -你好\N- Phil, how you doing? - How are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.47,0:39:52.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See the Pyramids Along the Nile - Patti Page
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.47,0:39:52.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,? See the pyramids along the Nile ?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.01,0:39:51.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,菲尔・泰斯塔\N1981年3月15日于自家门廊被一枚钉子炸弹炸死
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.91,0:39:53.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好  弗兰克\NHow you doing, Frank?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.62,0:39:58.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,? Watch the sun rise on a tropic isle ?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.35,0:39:59.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弗兰克・辛德文\N1980年10月29日身中三枪死于巷子内
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.83,0:40:04.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,? Just remember, darling, all the while ?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.26,0:40:05.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢  维托\NThank you, Vito.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.57,0:40:08.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,? You belong to me... ?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.25,0:40:09.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你好  弗兰克  -你好\N- Hi. Frank. - Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.85,0:40:11.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要来点什么吗\NWhat can I get for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.78,0:40:14.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先给我上杯酒吧\NI'm just gonna get the wine now.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.10,0:40:16.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.84,0:40:18.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有需要尽管叫我\NJust call me if you need anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.14,0:40:19.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的\NI will.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.15,0:40:26.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-慢用  弗兰克  -谢谢\N- Help yourself, Frank. - Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.24,0:40:29.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,情况变了\NThings change.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.81,0:40:36.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-她是新来的吧  -对\N- She's the new one, right? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.85,0:40:39.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她是个好姑娘  好姑娘\NA nice kid. Nice kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.99,0:40:40.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是啊\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.65,0:40:48.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,? I'll be so alone without you ?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.40,0:40:53.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么时候都不应该离开你的妻子\NNo time is a good time to leave your wife,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.98,0:40:58.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,汽车旅馆
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.14,0:40:55.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我就是那时候离开妻子的\Nbut that's when I left mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.48,0:41:04.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阿德斯里埃克斯汽车旅馆\N授权人签字
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.19,0:41:06.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,埃拉  最近还好吗\NIra, what's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.45,0:41:08.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-挺好的  你呢  -我也是\N- Good. All well? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.30,0:41:12.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-有遇到什么麻烦吗  -没有  一切顺利\N- Any problems? - No. Everything's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.26,0:41:13.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.52,0:41:17.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就停在这辆凯迪拉克后面\NRight after this Caddy, pull over.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.86,0:41:21.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到了  美丽皮草店\NThere it is. Fair Furriers.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.09,0:41:23.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,美丽皮草店
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.58,0:41:24.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他在等你\NHe's expecting you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.85,0:41:40.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,美丽皮草店
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.77,0:41:52.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,菲尔  你的店真不错\NPhil, you got a nice shop here.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.96,0:41:53.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢\NThanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.90,0:41:55.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人们喜欢来这里逛\NPeople like to come to this store.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.98,0:41:58.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但你儿子真是个瘪三\NBut your kid is a real sfigato.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.37,0:42:01.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,明白吗  他很讨人厌\NYou understand? He's a pain in the ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.22,0:42:03.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他太野了  你得管管他\NHe's a wild kid. You gotta learn to control him.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.77,0:42:04.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你不管\NAnd if you don't,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.77,0:42:07.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就再也没人想来这里逛了\Nnobody's gonna want to shop here anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.17,0:42:10.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你的生意不好  对我也没有好处\NIf it's not good for you, it's not good for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.92,0:42:12.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你明白我的意思吧\NYou understand what I'm saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.89,0:42:14.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗素  他给你惹麻烦了  我向你道歉\NI want to apologize, Russell, for the aggravation.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.00,0:42:18.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这份是我和罗素送的  那份是你和弗兰克送的\NThis is from Russell and I. That's from you and Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.40,0:42:20.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个是我们俩送的\NThis one'll be from you and me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.33,0:42:22.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要不送把宝宝汤匙吧\NWell, what about a baby spoon?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.57,0:42:24.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她要宝宝汤匙有什么用\NWhat's she gonna do with a baby spoon?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.09,0:42:25.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-他们还没结婚  -生个孩子就能用了\N- They're not even married. - Have a baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.39,0:42:26.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们都还没结婚呢\NThey're not even married yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.98,0:42:28.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我向你保证  罗素\NI give you my word, Russ.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.41,0:42:30.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-好的  你的话我信  菲尔  -谢谢\N- All right. Your word's good, Phil. - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.89,0:42:32.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好了  我们走吧  女士们\NOkay, let's go, girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.60,0:42:34.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-完事了  -是的  弄完了\N- Okay, we're done? - Yes, we're done.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.22,0:42:36.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在搞什么\NWhat are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.04,0:42:40.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你什么时候才能机灵点  -什么\N- When the hell are you gonna wise up, huh? - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.37,0:42:55.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好样的  不愧是我女儿\NThere we go. That's my girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.06,0:42:57.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天呐\NOh, my God!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.15,0:43:04.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太棒了\NYes!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.37,0:43:09.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,佩琪\NPeggy.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.40,0:43:12.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,过来一下\NCome over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.82,0:43:17.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我说不好  我...\NI don't know. I don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.36,0:43:19.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我感觉她不喜欢我\NI get the feeling she don't like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.81,0:43:21.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-她好像有点怕我  -不  不是的\N- Like she's afraid of me. - No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.34,0:43:22.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她就是这样\NThat's the way she is.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.02,0:43:24.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有时她也会怕我\NShe's afraid of me at times too.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.37,0:43:26.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她就是有点敏感\NSo, uh, it's just she's a sensitive kid,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.84,0:43:27.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,敏感而已\Nbut that's all it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.84,0:43:29.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我能理解她怕我\NI can understand her being afraid of me,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.46,0:43:31.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是她不应该怕你  弗兰克\Nbut she shouldn't be scared of you, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.08,0:43:32.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是\NNo, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.06,0:43:34.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有时她会在报纸上看到关于我的报道\NAnd then she hears about me in the papers sometimes...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.45,0:43:35.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-真的吗  -是啊\N- Really? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.84,0:43:37.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要跟自己的孩子亲一点  弗兰克\NYou gotta be close to your kids, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.11,0:43:39.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们很亲近\NI am. I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.31,0:43:40.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有孩子是你的福分\NYou're blessed to have them.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.47,0:43:42.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,凯丽和我没有小孩  我跟你说过\NI mean, Carrie and I can't have kids. I told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.66,0:43:45.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你真是有福气  有福气\NBut you're blessed. You're blessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.69,0:43:47.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,叫她一下  叫她过来\NCall her. Call her. Tell her to come over.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.45,0:43:49.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,佩琪宝贝  过来\NSweetheart. Peggy. Come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.53,0:43:50.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,过来\NCome here.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.04,0:43:58.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-过来  -到罗素伯伯这里来\N- Come here. - Come over by Uncle Russ.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.86,0:44:01.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你好吗  -挺好的\N- How are you? - Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.62,0:44:04.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道为什么上帝会把天空造这么高吗\NDo you know why God made the sky so high?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.96,0:44:06.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不知道\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.49,0:44:10.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这样小鸟在天上飞的时候\NSo that the little birdies don't bunk their head on it
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.31,0:44:11.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,才不会碰到头啊\Nwhen they're flying around.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.28,0:44:14.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可爱吧\NIsn't that cute?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.52,0:44:15.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是一个小笑话\NA little joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.23,0:44:17.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不好笑吗\NIsn't that funny?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.64,0:44:19.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要吃点糖果什么的吗\NYou want some candy or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.82,0:44:20.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不用了\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.35,0:44:22.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  你们不想吃糖\NNo, you guys don't want any candy.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.27,0:44:26.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,需要我为你做点什么吗\NThere's nothing I could do for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.43,0:44:27.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不用了\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.27,0:44:29.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,需要的话你要告诉罗素伯伯\NWell, if there is, you let Uncle Russell know.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.92,0:44:30.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.11,0:44:32.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,回去玩吧\NGo back. Have some fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.31,0:44:36.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,知道我什么意思了吗\NYou see what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.79,0:44:38.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,明白我的感觉了吗\NYou see that feeling I get?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.30,0:44:40.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她就是  腼腆而已\NShe's just... She's shy, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.39,0:44:42.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她没有恶意\NShe... She don't mean nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.60,0:44:44.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有时候  父母离婚了\NSometimes, when the parents get divorced,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.03,0:44:47.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,孩子们就会迷茫  然后他们会充满恨意\Nthe kids get all confused, and then they get resentful
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.83,0:44:49.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不知道该向谁发泄\Nand they don't know who to take it out on,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.62,0:44:51.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或是站哪边\Nor, you know, which side, or...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.38,0:44:52.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  你说得对\NNo, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.43,0:44:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是这一点我很幸运\NI'm lucky in that way because
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.47,0:44:57.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为琳妮和玛丽相处得很好\NReenie and Mary, they get along like gangbusters,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.83,0:45:00.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,孩子们轮流在两家住  没什么问题\Nso the kids go back and forth with no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.35,0:45:02.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要把家人留在身边  留意这一点\NKeep your family close. Keep an eye on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.41,0:45:04.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就是提醒你一下\NAnyway, I'm just telling you, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.21,0:45:06.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想我就是运气好\NI mean, I'm... I'm just lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.58,0:45:08.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是啊\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.22,0:45:12.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,工会的工作怎么样\NHow's it going with the union?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.47,0:45:14.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,工会是世界上最好的\NThe union's the best in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.94,0:45:16.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你喜欢  -是啊  只是...\N- You like it, huh? - Yeah, well, it's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.78,0:45:19.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想要找个稳定点的工作  不过\NI mean, I wish I had something more steady, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.90,0:45:20.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是有些\NYeah, it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.23,0:45:23.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-管理怎么样  -好啊\N- How about organizing? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.55,0:45:25.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我想干那个  可是  -怎么\N- I would like to do that. But... - Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.37,0:45:26.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很多人都等着呢\Nthere's a long line.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.07,0:45:29.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-换句话说  等候名单很长  -是\N- A long waiting list, if you will. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.15,0:45:33.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的一个朋友遇到了一点麻烦\NWell, a friend of ours is having a little trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.76,0:45:36.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-高层的朋友  -谁啊\N- Friend at the top. - Who's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.26,0:45:37.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,高层\NThe top.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.62,0:45:39.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,霍法\NHoffa?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.90,0:45:40.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嗯\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.25,0:45:42.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,之前我听说\NI heard the other day
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.12,0:45:45.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有人要用水管揍他\Nthat some guys tried to pipe him
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.25,0:45:47.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-因为一个工人的赔偿问题  -是的\N- because of a workman's comp case. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.48,0:45:49.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听说他把他们打得落花流水\NYeah, I heard he beat the shit out of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.89,0:45:51.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是  可他那样能撑多久呢\NYeah, but how long is he gonna keep doing that?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.00,0:45:53.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,总有这事儿那事儿\NThings are gonna keep happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.22,0:45:55.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他身边需要一个可靠的人\NHe needs somebody he can trust around him.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.32,0:45:57.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一个可以一直跟着他的人\NSomebody to be with him all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.60,0:45:58.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.57,0:46:04.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我让麦基接电话\NLet me put McGee on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.89,0:46:06.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,喂\NHello.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.90,0:46:09.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的朋友  你好吗\NHiya, my friend. How are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.40,0:46:13.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我找来了我跟你说过的那个年轻人\NListen, I got that kid I was talking to you about here.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.78,0:46:16.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我让他接电话  你跟他说  好吗\NI'm gonna put him on the phone, let you talk to him, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.91,0:46:17.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.99,0:46:20.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好\NHello.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.36,0:46:23.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-是弗兰克吧  -是我\N- Is that Frank? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.03,0:46:25.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弗兰克你好  我是吉米・霍法\NHiya, Frank. This is Jimmy Hoffa.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.20,0:46:26.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好  很高兴认识你\NYeah, yeah. Glad to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.89,0:46:29.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也很高兴认识你  虽然是在电话上\NWell, glad to meet you, too, even if it's over the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.69,0:46:33.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听说你刷房子\NI heard you paint houses.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.17,0:46:36.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的  先生  是的\NYes. Yes, sir, I... I do. I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.51,0:46:37.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我还\NAnd I, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.99,0:46:39.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,自己做木工\NI also do my own carpentry.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.20,0:46:41.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很高兴你这么说\NI'm glad to hear that.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.55,0:46:44.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听说你是工会的兄弟\NI understand you're a brother of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.32,0:46:47.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的  先生  从1947年就在107号地方工会了\NYes, sir. Local 107. Since 1947.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.67,0:46:49.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是吧\NYeah! You know, uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.46,0:46:51.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的朋友对你评价非常高\Nour friend speaks very highly of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.79,0:46:53.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢\NWell, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.43,0:46:57.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-他这个人要求可不低  -我尽力而为\N- He's not an easy man to please. - Well, I do my best.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.26,0:46:58.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有这么个情况\NWell, you know, there's a situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.86,0:47:02.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如今  年轻人不知道吉米・霍法是谁\NNowadays, young people, they don't know who Jimmy Hoffa was.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.20,0:47:04.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们完全没概念\NThey don't have a clue.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.07,0:47:07.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们可能知道他消失了什么的\NI mean, maybe they know that he disappeared or something,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.96,0:47:09.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但仅此而已\Nbut that's about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.82,0:47:13.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可在当时  全国上下\NBut back then, there wasn't nobody in this country
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.80,0:47:11.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,吉米・霍法
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.10,0:47:15.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没人不知道吉米・霍法是谁\Nwho didn't know who Jimmy Hoffa was.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.07,0:47:16.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上帝保佑  吉米\NGod bless, Jimmy.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.58,0:47:18.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你做的一切  你是个真正的绅士\NEverything you've done, you're a real gentleman.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.60,0:47:19.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很好\NThat's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.54,0:47:22.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,50年代的时候  他和猫王一样受欢迎\NIn the '50s, he was as big as Elvis.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.26,0:47:26.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,60年代的时候  他和披头士一样受欢迎\NIn the '60s, he was like the Beatles.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.08,0:47:27.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,除了总统以外\NNext to the president,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.05,0:47:30.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是国内最有权力的人  无人可及\Nhe was like the most powerful man in the country. Bar none.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.03,0:47:31.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你如果买东西\NIf you got it,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.08,0:47:34.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,卡车会把东西送过去\Na truck brought it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.67,0:47:36.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,卡车司机工会
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.87,0:47:39.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你买食物  衣服\NIf you got your food, your clothing,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.02,0:47:42.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,药物  家用燃料\Nyour medicine, if you got fuel for your homes,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.30,0:47:44.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,工业用燃料\Nfuel for your industries,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.03,0:47:47.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,卡车会把东西送去给他们\Na truck brought it to them!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.96,0:47:52.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们卡车停下的那天\NThe day our trucks stop,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.41,0:47:53.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是美国停下的那天\NAmerica stops!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.53,0:47:59.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在出了点状况  弗兰克\NWell, there's a situation going on now, Frank,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.12,0:48:00.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,需要处理\Nthat needs to be attended to.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.06,0:48:03.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们想分裂工会\NYou know, they're trying to tear the union apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.82,0:48:06.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大公司和政府联手\NBig business and the government working together,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.21,0:48:06.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想要拉我们下马\Ntrying to pull us down.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.75,0:48:09.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大公司在进攻\NBig business is on the attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.56,0:48:11.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们来了  来势汹汹\NThey're coming! They're coming hard
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.60,0:48:13.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,长驱直入\Nand they're coming fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.06,0:48:15.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大公司和政府\NBig business and the government
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.03,0:48:18.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想要在我们的阶层里埋下异议的种子\Nare trying to sow the seeds of dissent among our ranks,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.08,0:48:22.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而此时我们正需要联合\Nat a time when we need unity!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.62,0:48:25.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们需要团结\NWe need solidarity!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.39,0:48:27.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想把这话写在空中\NI want to write it in the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.95,0:48:29.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,团结\NSolidarity!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.67,0:48:32.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,团结\NSolidarity!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.35,0:48:34.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,团结\NSolidarity!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.20,0:48:37.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想加入这场战斗吗\NYou wanna be a part of this fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.16,0:48:38.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的  先生\NYes, I do, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.62,0:48:41.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想成为这历史的一部分吗\NWould you like to be a part of this history?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.20,0:48:42.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的  我想\NYes, I would.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.25,0:48:45.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,无论你需要我做什么  我都随叫随到\NWhatever you need me to do, I'm available.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.74,0:48:47.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你明天能来芝加哥吗\NCan you come to Chicago tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.57,0:48:48.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可以  先生\NYes, I can, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.99,0:48:50.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那好  到时见\NAll right, then. See you then.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.01,0:48:57.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-他喜欢说话  对吗  -是的\N- He likes to talk, don't he? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.16,0:49:04.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还以为我是在跟巴顿将军说话\NThought I was talking to General Patton.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.00,0:49:11.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弗兰克  你过来的唯一原因是\NYou know, Frank, the only reason why you're here,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.84,0:49:14.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,海员工会  他们想和我们一样\Nthe Seafarers Union, they're signing up
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.23,0:49:19.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,俄罗斯人和土耳其人浴室
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.23,0:49:17.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,签约非工会的\Nthe same non-union cab drivers
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.11,0:49:18.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,出租车司机\Nas we want to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.91,0:49:20.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没人知道你是谁\NNobody knows who you are
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.90,0:49:24.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没人知道你在这做什么  好吗\Nand nobody knows what the fuck you're doing here. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.10,0:49:26.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-嗯  -只有你我知道你为何来此\N- Yeah. - You and I know why you're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.12,0:49:28.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们得签约这些司机\NWe gotta be able to sign these drivers up
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.91,0:49:32.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这样保罗・霍尔的工会就签约不了他们\Nso Paul Hall doesn't get 'em for his fucking union.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.02,0:49:34.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不知为何  女同性恋\NFor some reason, lesbians.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.52,0:49:36.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些司机大多都是该死的女同性恋\NMost of these drivers are fucking lesbians.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.52,0:49:38.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道为什么\NI have no reason why.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.57,0:49:40.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,保罗・霍尔四处宣传\NPaul Hall's running around
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.10,0:49:42.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说他可以比我们的哥们吉米\Nsaying that he's gonna get a better contract
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.32,0:49:44.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,提供一份更好的合同\Nthan our boy fucking Jimmy.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.22,0:49:46.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他就是个狗杂种\NHe's a cocksucker. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.54,0:49:50.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,吉米收买了戴利市长\NJimmy has Mayor fucking Daley in his pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.59,0:49:53.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们做什么警察都不会管\NThe cops are okay with whatever the fuck we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.05,0:49:55.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们不会帮我们把车推下水\NThey're not gonna help us push these cars in,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.38,0:49:58.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但他们也绝对不会让任何人阻止我们\Nbut they certainly are not gonna let anybody fucking stop us.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.60,0:49:59.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,懂吗\NOkay?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.76,0:50:21.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,用力  大伙儿用力\NCome on! All of you guys. Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.86,0:50:24.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把车子推下去  小心点\NLet's get this fucking thing in there. Watch yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.04,0:50:28.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太费劲了\NThis is a lot of work.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.57,0:50:30.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你有想过用糖果吗\NYeah, you ever think of using candy?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.34,0:50:31.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-什么  -糖果\N- What? - Candy.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.97,0:50:33.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,糖果是什么鬼\NWhat the fuck is candy?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.50,0:50:37.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,炸药  轻拿轻放
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.00,0:50:40.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,卢  把门打开\NHey, Lou, open the fucking gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.91,0:50:41.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,知道  知道\NI got it. I got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.66,0:50:44.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来  你把汽油拿着\NHere, you take the gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.35,0:51:03.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弗兰克  吉米有个特点\NFrank, there's one thing about Jimmy.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.36,0:51:05.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他不喜欢等人\NDon't ever make him wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.21,0:51:07.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你和他约好见面  你一定要准时到场\NIf you make a meeting with him, you get there on time.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.80,0:51:09.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最好是提前到\NBetter yet, get there early.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.24,0:51:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我必须强调这一点\NI can't stress this enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.72,0:51:14.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他觉得时间很可贵\NHis problem is that time is of essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.08,0:51:15.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是最重要的\NAnd that's the important thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.02,0:51:19.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我还要跟你说件事  吉米不喝酒\NI gotta tell you one more thing. Jimmy doesn't drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.34,0:51:21.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的  世界上最大的货运工会的老大\NYeah. The head of the largest trucking union in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.57,0:51:22.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他不喝酒\Nhe don't drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.50,0:51:23.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这事最糟的地方在于\NThe worst part about it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.94,0:51:26.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他不允许别人在他身边喝酒\Nhe doesn't allow anybody to drink around him.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.57,0:51:32.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有件事\NAnother thing about him,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.95,0:51:35.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,吉米讨厌西瓜\NJimmy hates fucking watermelon.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.33,0:51:40.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我们喜欢西瓜\NBut we're gonna like watermelon.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.80,0:51:42.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,吉米  你当时真该去看看\NJimmy, you shoulda seen it,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.73,0:51:44.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,慢慢沉下水\Nsinking in the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.34,0:51:48.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一辆接一辆  我敢打赌  等他们隔天醒来\NOne by one. I bet you, when they woke up the next morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.59,0:51:50.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那些该死的出租车司机\Nthose fucking cab drivers,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.35,0:51:51.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们去找自己的出租车\Nthey went to look for their cabs,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.93,0:51:53.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们根本不知道发生了什么\Nthey didn't know what the fuck hit 'em.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.02,0:51:55.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真是个好主意  乔伊\NThat's a great idea, Joey.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.08,0:51:57.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好主意\NGreat idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.30,0:51:59.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是我想出来的\NWell, it wasn't my idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.92,0:52:02.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我哥们弗兰克  是他的主意\NMy man Frank. It was his idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.66,0:52:04.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我跟你说\NLet me tell you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.01,0:52:06.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弗兰克去了码头  他接管了码头\NFrank hit that pier, he took over the pier.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.98,0:52:09.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不管他叫他们做什么  不管他说什么\NWhatever he told them to do, whatever he said,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.08,0:52:10.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们都照做\Nthey did it, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.51,0:52:14.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我从没见过任何人像他那样穿过人群\NI never seen a guy walk through a crowd like he does.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.92,0:52:16.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他一个人都不碰\NHe doesn't touch a fucking person!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.30,0:52:18.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所有人都自觉让路\NEverybody gets out of the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.05,0:52:19.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没开玩笑  我发誓\NI'm not kidding you. I swear.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.52,0:52:21.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那些人和他素不相识  就像\NGuys he never met in his life. You know, it was like...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.84,0:52:23.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就像摩西  记得摩西吗\Nlike Moses. Remember Moses?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.97,0:52:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他走进海洋还是大海\NWhen he walked into the ocean, the sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.02,0:52:28.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不管是什么  水面就分开了\Nwhatever the fuck it was, and it opened up!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.39,0:52:31.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是他  相信我  吉米  他有那能力\NThat's him. I'm telling you. Jimmy, he's got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.53,0:52:32.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你觉得如何\NSo, what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.51,0:52:34.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你还需要他在这待几天吗\NYou need him a couple of days more?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.77,0:52:37.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的  我们还有一些零碎的事要处理\NYeah, we gotta clear up a few dribs and drabs.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.73,0:52:41.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们真喜欢西瓜啊\NYou guys sure like watermelon.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.95,0:52:42.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想吃一口吗\NWant a bite?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.85,0:52:44.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,决不\NNot on your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.36,0:52:48.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你当时在场  你亲眼看到了\NYou were there. You saw it firsthand.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.66,0:52:50.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那些人不是工会\NThose guys ain't union.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.89,0:52:54.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们就像是纳粹同谋  在战场后方行动\NThey're like Nazi collaborators, operating behind the lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.86,0:52:57.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你懂的  你打过仗  -没错\N- You know. You were in the war. - I sure do.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.13,0:53:03.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在战争期间  你从一个地方转移到另一个地方\NIn a war, you go from point A to point B.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.70,0:53:04.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有时候\NSometimes,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.51,0:53:08.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你会在路上洒一些啤酒\Nyou spill a little beer along the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.15,0:53:11.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你觉得这哲学有道理吗\NThat philosophy make sense to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.95,0:53:12.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然\NSure does.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.04,0:53:14.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很好\NGood.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.17,0:53:34.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,吉米  他不是因为喜欢我\NJimmy, he didn't make me stay in his suite
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.11,0:53:35.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而让我住他的套房\Nbecause he liked me.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.35,0:53:38.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他让我跟他一起住是因为他不想让我\NHe made me stay with him because he didn't want me
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.36,0:53:40.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,用我的名字在酒店登记\Nregistering in my name at the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.98,0:53:44.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这样  就没有证据证明我去过芝加哥\NThis way, there was no proof I was even in Chicago.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.69,0:53:57.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,加油  吉米  你落后好多\NCome on, Jimmy, you're way behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.44,0:53:58.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么都阻止不了她\NNothing stops her.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.57,0:54:01.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,芝加哥那事之后  我和吉米走得更近了\NAfter Chicago, Jimmy and I got close.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.42,0:54:02.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,老婆们也相处得很融洽\NThe wives hit it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.14,0:54:04.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为吉米和约瑟芬的孩子\NAnd with Jimmy and Josephine's kids
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.84,0:54:06.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大多已成年  离开了家\Nmostly grown up and out of the house,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.85,0:54:08.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们从我们孩子身上也获得不少乐趣\Nthey got a kick out of our kids too.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.63,0:54:10.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,吉米  佩琪  来拍张照\NJimmy, Peggy, let's get a picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.37,0:54:12.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"约"・霍法
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.78,0:54:11.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好  快来\NOh. Yes. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.76,0:54:13.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尤其是佩琪\NEspecially Peggy.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.40,0:54:16.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她和吉米  他们一下就喜欢上了对方\NShe and Jimmy, they fell for each other right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.93,0:54:20.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道比起拍照我更喜欢什么吗\NYou know what I like even better than getting my picture took?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.76,0:54:21.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.80,0:54:25.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,惊喜吧\NSurprise!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.98,0:54:26.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,佩琪\NPeggy!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.71,0:54:28.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对佩琪来说  吉米不像罗素\NTo Peggy, Jimmy wasn't like Russ,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.16,0:54:30.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,韦尔冰淇淋店
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.95,0:54:30.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不像瘦子也不像我\Nor Skinny or even me.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.89,0:54:34.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉各位  这是买给我和佩琪的\NSorry, everybody. This is just for Peggy and I.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.17,0:54:36.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一方面  吉米没有绰号\NFor one thing, Jimmy didn't have a nickname
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.37,0:54:38.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,比如"剃刀"或者"钟楼怪人"\Nlike "The Razor," Or "The Hunchback,"
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.30,0:54:40.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或者"黄鼠狼"亦或者"悄悄话"\Nor "The Weasel," Or "Whispers."
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.90,0:54:42.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么不说谢谢\NSo what happened to "Thank you"?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.95,0:54:43.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢\NThank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.57,0:54:47.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有  对她来说  他是在帮助人\NAnd also, to her, he was helping people.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.17,0:54:49.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他在帮他们赚更多钱  过得更好\NHe was helping them make more money, live better lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.37,0:54:52.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他没有踩别人的手\NHe wasn't stomping on somebody's hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.71,0:54:56.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"如果你买东西  卡车会把东西送过去"\N"'If you have it, a truck brought it to you."
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.01,0:54:58.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是霍法先生说的\NThis is what Mr. Hoffa says.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.46,0:55:03.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,职业介绍日  1960年
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.91,0:55:01.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是卡车司机工会的主席\NHe's the president of the Teamsters Union
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.08,0:55:03.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,成员超过一百万\Nwith over a million members.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.33,0:55:06.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们都支持他因为他们有稳定的工作\NThey all support him because they have steady jobs,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.08,0:55:08.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是吉米・霍法的朋友
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.23,0:55:08.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,丰厚的薪水以及退休后的养老金\Ngreat pay and a pension for when they retire.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.56,0:55:12.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,卡车司机养老基金\NThe Teamster Pension Fund
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.01,0:55:14.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有八十亿美元\Nhad eight billion dollars in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.18,0:55:18.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,全部都由吉米控制\NAnd Jimmy had complete control over every bit of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.61,0:55:20.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沙丘酒店
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.14,0:55:19.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这模型是不是很美\NIsn't this a beautiful presentation?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.91,0:55:23.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只想要一笔过渡性贷款  吉米\NI mean, a bridge loan is really all I'm asking, Jimmy.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.73,0:55:26.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不会把工会成员的养老金\NI'm not gonna piss away my members' pension dough
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.43,0:55:27.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,投资在风险过大的项目上\Non something too risky.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.66,0:55:29.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这没有风险  吉米\NThis is not a risk, Jimmy.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.56,0:55:31.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,《明斯基的荒唐事》这个节目是我的\NI got Minsky's Follies.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.96,0:55:34.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,赌城大道第一个露乳舞女秀是我的\NI got the first topless act on the Strip.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.32,0:55:35.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,相信我  我们在那的生意可好了\NI'm telling you, we're booming in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.80,0:55:37.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,酒都卖不过来...\NI can't get the drinks out...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.04,0:55:38.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就想要建一个高尔夫球场\NJust asking for a golf course.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.61,0:55:40.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道我从未让你损失一分钱\NYou know you never lost a dime with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.15,0:55:42.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,吉米  我们会很感激\NJimmy, we'd really just appreciate
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.06,0:55:43.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你帮杰克做的事的\Nwhatever you could do to help Jake along here.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.86,0:55:46.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只需要150万的完工保证金\NOne-five is all I need for a completion bond.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.12,0:55:51.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧  去拿钱吧\NOkay. Okay. Go to the bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.34,0:55:53.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢  这个项目会大获成功的\NThank you. It's gonna be a big success.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.87,0:55:55.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你  吉米  你是王子\NThank you, Jimmy. You're a prince.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.92,0:55:58.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你是好人  -是的  我是好人\N- You're a mensch. - Yeah, I'm a mensch.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.41,0:56:08.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,多亏了霍法先生\NAnd, because of Mr. Hoffa,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.66,0:56:11.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,工人生病时有医疗保险\Nworkers have medical insurance for when they get sick,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.75,0:56:15.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们知道退休后  不会挨饿\Nand know when they retire, they're not going to go hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.86,0:56:19.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当时有太多的文书工作\NThere was so much paperwork back then
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.03,0:56:21.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,吉米只能用一个叫艾伦・多夫曼的年轻人开的\Nthat Jimmy had to use an insurance company
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.37,0:56:24.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一家保险公司来处理贷款\Nthat was run by this kid, Allen Dorfman, to work out the loans.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.68,0:56:26.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  一分钱都不借\NNo, no, nothing for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.13,0:56:28.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,下次  试试口气好一点\NNext time, try asking a little bit fucking nicer.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.51,0:56:33.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾伦・多夫曼  1979年\N在芝加哥的一处停车场头中八枪身亡
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.61,0:56:35.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后呢  进展如何\NAnd? And? How'd it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.73,0:56:38.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,情况一度很危急\NIt was a little touch and go for a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.30,0:56:40.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-但是最后还是顺利达成了  -很好\N- But at the end, fine. - Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.10,0:56:41.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是罗素让吉米\NIt was Russ who got Jimmy
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.24,0:56:43.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,给戈特利布这样的人贷款\Nto give guys like Gottlieb the loans,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.31,0:56:45.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他能分到一成\Nand, you know, he would get like 10% of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.32,0:56:48.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也不知道  也许更多\NOr whatever, you know. Maybe more.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.49,0:56:51.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,听着  你告诉马尔特杜佐我很感激\NListen, you tell Marteduzzo from me that I appreciate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.89,0:56:53.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人人都会感激\NAnd everybody's gonna appreciate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.58,0:56:54.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是好事\NIt's a good thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.50,0:56:55.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,行  我会的\NOkay. I'll do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.49,0:56:57.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那时  你不能去普通银行\NBack then, you couldn't go to regular banks
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.51,0:56:59.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为钱是用来赌博的\Nbecause the money was for gambling.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.31,0:57:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,千真万确  就是这样  我没开玩笑  不能去\NGod's truth, that's what it was. I'm serious. You couldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.00,0:57:03.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以黑手党  他们怎么办呢\NSo the Mob, what did they do?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.81,0:57:05.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们找卡车司机工会贷款\NThey went to the Teamsters for the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.74,0:57:07.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是卡车司机工会介入其中\NIt was the Teamsters that stepped in
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.59,0:57:09.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们借出的钱打造了拉斯维加斯\Nand lent the money that built Las Vegas.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.86,0:57:11.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-这是红木  -别  比利\N- This is the mahogany... - Don't, Billy.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.37,0:57:12.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-别碰  -我不碰\N- Don't touch the stuff. - I won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.72,0:57:14.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-该上哪去上哪去  -好\N- Just go where you gotta go. - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.01,0:57:17.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当时的生意多得让人应接不暇\NThere was more business than anybody could handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.41,0:57:19.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以吉米把一些生意\NSo Jimmy had to shove some of the deals
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.16,0:57:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,塞给了他老婆约\Noff on to his wife Jo,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.91,0:57:23.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她完全不知道\Nwho had no idea she had 22%
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.13,0:57:24.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她拥有一个叫"太阳谷"的\Nof a Florida land deal
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.13,0:57:25.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,佛州土地交易公司22%的股份\Ncalled "Sun Valley,"
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.90,0:57:27.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,几艘包租渔船\Nsome charter fishing boats,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.63,0:57:29.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以及一个带私家雪山的滑雪度假屋\Nand a ski lodge with its own mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.52,0:57:38.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,吉米有个客户叫山姆・詹卡纳  绰号"莫莫"\NOne of Jimmy's clients was Sam "Momo" Giancana,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.61,0:57:40.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他和肯尼迪家族是世交\Nwho was friends with the Kennedys from back
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.27,0:57:42.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这两家自约翰・肯尼迪的父亲在禁酒令期间走私酒\Nwhen Jack's father made his fortune with the Italians
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.99,0:57:45.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,和意大利人一起赚大钱时就认识了\Nas a bootlegger during Prohibition.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.19,0:57:47.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,露希尔・亨特\N刘易斯・康宁汉姆\N玛丽昂・希克斯\N德妮思・鲍威尔\N艾米特・伍兹
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.50,0:57:49.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,莫莫和辛纳屈跟肯尼迪家族混\NMomo, Sinatra hung out together with the Kennedys.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.65,0:57:49.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾米特・伍兹
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.27,0:57:51.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,莫莫和肯尼迪\NMomo and Kennedy,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.12,0:57:54.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不管你信不信  甚至有同一个女友\Nbelieve it or not, even had the same girlfriend.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.71,0:57:56.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在同一时期\NTogether. At the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.41,0:57:58.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真是太疯狂了\NTalk about crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.29,0:58:01.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以对黑手党来说  帮助乔・肯尼迪\NSo it was easy for the Mob to help Joe Kennedy
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.43,0:58:04.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让他儿子当选总统很容易  非常容易\Nget his son elected president. That was easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.62,0:58:06.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们操控了选票\NThey just punched up the vote a little
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.53,0:58:08.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,确保他在伊利诺伊州胜出\Nto make sure that he won in Illinois.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.56,0:58:08.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雷蒙德・克拉克
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.07,0:58:12.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾米特・伍兹
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.64,0:58:14.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,作为交换\NIn exchange for that,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.35,0:58:17.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,新上台的总统要把卡斯特罗从古巴赶下台\Nthe new president was supposedly gonna get Castro out of Cuba
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.58,0:58:20.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这样我们的人就能拿回他们的赌场\Nso our guys could get their casinos back,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.35,0:58:22.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,赛马场  捕虾船\Nand race tracks, and shrimp boats,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.43,0:58:23.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以及他们在哈瓦那\Nand everything else that they had,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.68,0:58:26.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,曾拥有的一切\Nand owned down there from Havana back.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.34,0:58:28.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过那事没成\NBut that... that didn't happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.01,0:58:35.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,投民主党
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.60,0:58:39.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,意大利人想让爱尔兰人肯尼迪当总统\NThe Italians wanted Kennedy the Irishman for president,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.79,0:58:41.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们如愿了\Nand that's what they got.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.29,0:58:46.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,习惯吧  因为以后我们每时每刻都得看到了\NGet used to it, because we're gonna be seeing it 24/7.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.37,0:58:47.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,狗娘养的\NSon of a bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.68,0:58:48.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,该死的肯尼迪家族\NGoddamn Kennedys.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.94,0:58:50.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我在看该死的肯尼迪家族\NI'm looking at the goddamn Kennedys.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.38,0:58:52.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,吉米  孩子们都在呢  注意言辞\NJimmy, the kids. Language.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.54,0:58:54.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有什么差别\NWhat difference does it make?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.54,0:58:56.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们迟早都要学会的\NI mean, they gotta learn sooner or later.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.05,0:58:57.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们要和这些人开战\NWe're going to war with these people.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.35,0:58:59.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,开战\NWar!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.07,0:59:02.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我已经说了无数次了\NIf I said it once, I said it a thousand times,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.27,0:59:03.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不在乎他们是不是爱尔兰人\NI don't care they're Irish.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.50,0:59:06.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不在乎他们是不是天主教徒\NI don't care they're Catholic.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.05,0:59:09.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果要说这辈子有谁你不能信\NIf there's one person you can't trust in this life,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.60,0:59:10.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就是百万富翁的孩子\Nit's millionaires' kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.95,0:59:12.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你说得对  吉米\NYou're right, Jimmy.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.09,0:59:15.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尤其是那个小杂种\NEspecially that little son of a bitch.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.80,0:59:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是说你不记得\NAre you saying you don't remember
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.32,0:59:21.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你帮过约翰尼・迪奥吗\Ndoing any favors for Johnny Dio,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.40,0:59:25.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗伯特・肯尼迪
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.46,0:59:23.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还是说你不记得你们的对话\Nor you don't remember the conversation?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.67,0:59:28.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是说  我已经尽力回忆了\NI'm saying, to the best of my recollection,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.38,0:59:30.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,根据我的回忆\NI must recall on my memory,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.11,0:59:32.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想不起来了\NI cannot remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.24,0:59:37.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那这两万块是哪来的\NThen where did this $20,000 come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.80,0:59:41.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,个人的\NIndividuals.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.12,0:59:44.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哪些个人  霍法先生\NWhich individuals, Mr. Hoffa?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.30,0:59:51.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,未经核查的情况下  这笔我借的钱\NOff hand, that particular amount of money I borrowed,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.27,0:59:53.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我目前也想不起是找谁借的\NI don't know at this particular moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.76,0:59:59.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是根据我取得的贷款记录\NBut the record of my loans, which I requested, I have,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.66,1:00:01.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在这段时间内\Nand out of all the moneys I loaned
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.92,1:00:06.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我贷款的所有钱  都投资给了这些企业\Nduring this period of time I went into these ventures.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.90,1:00:13.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,该死的肯尼迪家族\NThose goddamn Kennedys,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.63,1:00:15.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们总是得偿所愿\Nthey get what they want!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.07,1:00:15.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,吉米  吉米  孩子们在呢\NJimmy. Jimmy, the kids.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.97,1:00:17.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他已经让我\NHim and all the bullshit problems
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.83,1:00:19.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-处处受制  -吉米\N- he put me through already. - Jimmy.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.69,1:00:21.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我得走了  别指望我看这个\NI gotta go. You don't expect me to look at this.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.81,1:00:23.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不指望\NNo, I don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.45,1:00:25.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对罗素这样的人来说\NFor guys like Russ,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.77,1:00:27.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那最好不过了\Nit couldn't have been better.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.26,1:00:28.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,支持肯尼迪当总统
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.47,1:00:28.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是说  罗素\NI mean, Russ,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.38,1:00:29.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,支持肯尼迪当总统
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.93,1:00:31.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,肯尼迪当选他也有出力\Noh, yeah, he did his part for getting Kennedy elected,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.68,1:00:35.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,支持肯尼迪当总统
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.85,1:00:32.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这点毫无疑问\Nthat's for sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.07,1:00:34.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在做什么  我叫你把它...\NWhat are you doing? I told you to put it...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.33,1:00:36.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我叫你贴到所有杆子上\NI told you to put them on every pole.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.13,1:00:37.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你还在这瞎转\NYou're still walking around.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.23,1:00:38.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以约翰・肯尼迪\NSo what's the first thing
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.19,1:00:41.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为了感谢芝加哥的帮助做的第一件事是什么\Nthat Jack Kennedy does to thank Chicago for all their help?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.25,1:00:44.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他让他的垃圾弟弟上位了\NHe puts his shitass brother in there,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.39,1:00:45.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那个预科学校混蛋\Nthat little prep school punk,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.72,1:00:48.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他让他成了司法部长\Nand he winds up making him attorney general.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.28,1:00:53.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,鲍比上任后做的第一件事是什么\NAnd what's the first thing Bobby does?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.10,1:00:55.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他不仅对付吉米\NHe goes after not just Jimmy,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.14,1:00:57.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从某种程度上讲  你也能理解\Nwhich in a way you could understand.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.84,1:00:59.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,吉米无比厌恶肯尼迪家族\NI mean, Jimmy hated the Kennedys so much
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.43,1:01:02.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以至于他从工会拿了五十万给尼克松\Nhe gave Nixon $500,000 in Teamster cash.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.56,1:01:05.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但鲍比还去对付詹卡纳\NBut Bobby also goes after Giancana,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.25,1:01:08.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,马切洛  特拉菲坎特  以及其他所有\NMarcello, Trafficante, and all the other guys
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.61,1:01:11.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当初帮他哥哥入住白宫的人\Nwho put his brother in the White House in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.86,1:01:15.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是在干什么\NWhat's that about?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.32,1:01:16.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弗兰克\NFrank.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.84,1:01:18.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-谢谢  -圣诞快乐\N- Thank you. - Merry Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.07,1:01:19.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是漏掉了什么吗\NAm I missing something?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.87,1:01:21.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢你  凯丽\NThank you, Carrie.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.35,1:01:27.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-太漂亮了  -真美\N- That's gorgeous. - Beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.49,1:01:30.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,戴着它健健康康  我们爱你\NWear it in the best of health. We love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.63,1:01:34.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是给佩琪的\NOkay, now this one is for Peggy
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.13,1:01:37.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,罗素伯伯送的  圣诞快乐  亲爱的\Nfrom Uncle Russell. Merry Christmas, my love.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.69,1:01:39.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看呀\NOh, look at those.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.24,1:01:43.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太好了\NSo nice!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.06,1:01:45.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我听说你喜欢滑冰\NI heard you like to skate.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.44,1:01:47.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你该说什么\NWhat do you say?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.47,1:01:50.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.61,1:01:53.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在我和罗素伯伯可以带你去滑冰了\NNow me and Uncle Russell could take you ice skating.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.11,1:01:54.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想圣诞老人\NI think Santa Claus left you
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.62,1:01:56.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在里面还给你留了点东西\Na little something extra in there too.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.90,1:02:03.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你该对罗素伯伯说什么\NWhat do you say to Uncle Russell?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.59,1:02:06.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你该说什么\NWhat do you say?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.43,1:02:10.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弗兰克  没关系\NFrank, it's all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.53,1:02:14.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她已经说了一次谢谢了  这就够了\NShe said thank you once. That's enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.28,1:02:20.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为鲍比是司法部长  他们把我们盯得很紧\NWith Bobby as attorney general, I mean, they were all over us.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.42,1:02:22.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们不能在电话里说事\NI mean, we couldn't talk on the phone
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.06,1:02:24.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为我们知道有人窃听\Nbecause we knew it was being bugged.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.19,1:02:26.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你什么都不能做  哪也不能去\NYou couldn't do nothing. You couldn't go nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.05,1:02:27.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么都做不了\NYou couldn't do anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.38,1:02:29.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,总之情况特别糟糕\NIt was a bad, bad, bad situation.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.37,1:02:31.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后吉米  算了\NAnd then Jimmy... Forget it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.84,1:02:34.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,鲍比  现在作为司法部长  他有权力\NBobby, now as attorney general, he has the power
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.49,1:02:36.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,送任何人进监狱  毋庸置疑\Nto send anybody to jail, and no question about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.83,1:02:39.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,吉米在鲍比的打击对象名单上名列前茅\NAnd Jimmy was at the top of Bobby's hit list.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.29,1:02:41.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他甚至组建了一只专门的"抓捕霍法小队"\NHe even set up a special "Get Hoffa Squad,"
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.91,1:02:43.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他找来了联调局\Nwhere he had his own guys from the FBI,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.71,1:02:45.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有国税局的人夜以继日地工作\Nthe IRS working 'round the clock.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.63,1:02:48.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们唯一的工作就是送吉米・霍法进监狱\NTheir only job was to put Jimmy Hoffa in jail.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.83,1:02:50.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是认真的  他们只干了这事\NI'm serious. That's all they did.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.96,1:02:57.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这房间里全是该死的蠢货\NI am sitting in a room full of fuckin' idiots.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.62,1:03:01.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一群傻逼\NYou dumb motherfuckers!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.31,1:03:02.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们知道你们做了什么吗\NYou know what you did?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.90,1:03:05.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们找来约翰尼・奥鲁克的孩子\NYou take Johnny O'Rourke's kid
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.86,1:03:07.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们让他\Nand you put him on
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.58,1:03:10.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,成为总组织者\Nas general organizer,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.31,1:03:13.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,支付了他3.6万\Npay him 36 fucking grand,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.73,1:03:15.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,与此同时\Nat the same time,
