Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.65,1:10:24.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧  这也不能怪谁啊  这...\NOkay. Well, you can't blame anybody for that. That's...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.70,1:10:26.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我又没打算怪谁\NI'm not looking to blame anybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.18,1:10:28.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但真要怪谁的话  得怪肯尼迪小子们\NBut if there's any blame going around, it's the Kennedys.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.74,1:10:30.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我可以告诉你  是他的儿子害死了他\NHis kids killed him. Let me tell you that.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.63,1:10:33.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他还没死  但他快死了  快死了\NHe's not dead, but he's going. He's going.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.34,1:10:36.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们害死了他  他们能让任何人犯心脏病\NThey killed him. They'd give anybody a heart attack.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.38,1:10:46.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,久病后于1969年去世\N老约瑟夫・P・肯尼迪
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.16,1:11:12.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要去哪\NWhere are you going?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.20,1:11:14.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我去工作\NI'm going to work.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.42,1:11:16.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,回去睡觉吧\NGo back to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.59,1:11:51.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,杜维尔
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.99,1:12:09.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我能说的是  我们不会罢休\NAll I can say is that, we will not stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.01,1:12:12.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为我们已经坚持了五十年\NBecause we've been doing that for 50 years!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.93,1:12:14.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有什么好处\NWhat good does it do?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.91,1:12:17.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让律师去开开卡车\NLet the lawyers... Let the lawyers drive a truck.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.69,1:12:21.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们需要纸笔  需要印台\NThey need their pencils and papers and their ink pads.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.36,1:12:24.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那完全是另一回事了\NThat's... That's a whole other story.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.76,1:12:26.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我们会挺过去的\NBut we're gonna get through this.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.91,1:12:30.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们用什么法律狗屁打压我们\NWe're gonna get through this legal bullshit
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.16,1:12:32.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们会挺过去的\Nand garbage they're throwing at us.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.36,1:12:34.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们会挺过去的\NWe're gonna get through it because
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.70,1:12:34.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,新泽西卡车司机
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.32,1:12:37.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为呆子肯尼迪想要什么  并不意味着\N"Boobie" Kennedy wants something, that doesn't mean
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.61,1:12:39.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个纨绔子弟就能得手\Nthe rich boy is gonna get it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.59,1:12:40.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们明白我的意思吧\NYou understand what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.83,1:12:44.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不在乎他要什么  反正他得不到\NI don't care what he wants. He's not gonna get it!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.39,1:12:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他得不到  因为\NHe's not gonna get it because
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.60,1:12:53.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们是这个国家\Nwe are the biggest and best,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.58,1:12:56.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最庞大  最优秀\Nand most honest union
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.04,1:12:57.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最诚实的工会\Nin this country!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.30,1:12:59.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对  没错\NYeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.18,1:13:00.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就等着这个\NI waited for that!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.65,1:13:08.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们知道我今天要讲的关键词是什么\NAnd you know the operative word I'm talking about here.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.94,1:13:10.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-团结  -对\N- Solidarity. - Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.79,1:13:13.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,团结有效  对我们所有人都有效\NAnd it works. It works for all of us.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.07,1:13:17.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对我们的朋友弗兰克・菲茨西蒙斯有效\NAnd it works for our friend here, Frank Fitzsimmons!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.12,1:13:19.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这位是弗兰克・菲茨西蒙斯\NFrank Fitzsimmons here,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.30,1:13:22.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的执行副主席\Nmy executive vice president.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.88,1:13:26.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果有谁能胜任这份工作  那就是他\NIf there's anyone that can do this job, it's this man here.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.24,1:13:28.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有他为我保驾护航\NAnd with him at my back,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.77,1:13:31.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们一定会蒸蒸日上\Nwhere are we gonna go but up!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.84,1:13:34.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对吗  菲茨\NIs that right, Fitz?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.76,1:13:35.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,完全正确  吉米\NAll the way, Jimmy!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.77,1:13:50.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,霍法  霍法  霍法\NHoffa! Hoffa! Hoffa!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.77,1:13:53.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一个工会人\NA union man!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.94,1:13:56.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得他们喜欢菲茨\NYou know, I felt they liked Fitz.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.90,1:13:57.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,毋庸置疑\NNo two ways about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.96,1:14:00.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是  你提拔了菲茨\NYeah, you gave Fitz some buildup.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.47,1:14:02.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,希望他不会辜负你\NI mean, I hope he deserves it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.04,1:14:05.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么说  菲茨有什么不妥吗\NWhy? What's wrong with Fitz?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.39,1:14:09.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我说不好  我不想批评他\NI don't know. I don't want to knock the guy,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:09.47,1:14:10.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我也说不好\Nbut I... I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.65,1:14:13.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不用批评他  告诉我\NWell, you're not knocking him. Just tell me...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.10,1:14:14.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,告诉我你的感受\NTell me what you feel.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.36,1:14:17.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他很忠诚  这我可以确定\NI mean, he's a loyal guy, I'm sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.05,1:14:19.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是个好人\NHe's a nice guy,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.44,1:14:21.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但他不够敏锐  不够聪明\Nbut he ain't that sharp. He ain't that smart.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.81,1:14:23.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他还...\NAnd he's also like a...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.07,1:14:25.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他总打高尔夫球\NHe plays a lot of fucking golf, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.37,1:14:26.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他打高尔夫球\NHe plays golf?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.02,1:14:29.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那又如何  二把手就需要这样的\NSo what? That's what you want from a number two.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.56,1:14:31.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不需要太聪明的人\NYou don't want somebody too smart.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.68,1:14:34.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,需要一个好人  大家喜欢他\NYou want a nice guy. People like him, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.48,1:14:36.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不傻  但是个\NNot dumb, but somebody,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.55,1:14:37.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可以放心让他走在身后\Nyou know you can have walking behind you
Dialogue: 0,1:14:37.83,1:14:39.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而不怕被捅刀子的人\Nwithout getting knifed.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.20,1:14:43.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-希望你是对的  -我总是对的\N- Well, I hope you're right. - I'm always right.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.13,1:14:45.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我可以对菲茨可以放一百个心\NI can sleep like a babe with Fitz.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.24,1:14:49.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我担心的是矮子\NIt's the Little Guy I have to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.83,1:14:50.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道我说的是谁\NYou know what I'm saying.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.15,1:14:52.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-是  -是\N- Yeah. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:52.23,1:14:53.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,矮子\NThe Little Guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.44,1:14:54.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我担心的是他  -嗯\N- That's my worry. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.34,1:14:57.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那个王八蛋\NThat son of a bitch.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.46,1:15:00.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么了\NWhat's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.34,1:15:02.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没事  没事  你是对的\NNothing. Nothing. You're right.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.66,1:15:04.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是对的  是的\NI'm right. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.95,1:15:06.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你不会觉得困惑吧  -完全不会\N- You're not perplexed, are you? - Not at all. Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.91,1:15:10.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我和你说了我对菲茨的感受  至于普罗  你懂的\NI mean, I told you how I felt about Fitz. Pro. You know.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.45,1:15:12.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好  那就好  因为有时我觉得\NYeah. Good, because sometimes I feel
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.37,1:15:15.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只有我一个人看穿了那个狗杂种\NI'm the only one who sees right through that cocksucker.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.42,1:15:18.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,? 让我们举杯... ?\N? So let's raise a glass... ?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.12,1:15:18.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-他是个坏人  -他是个坏人\N- He's a bad guy. - He's a bad guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.37,1:15:22.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,? 敬最伟大的人 ?\N? To the greatest guy ?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.95,1:15:28.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,? 能有他是560号地方工会之幸 ?\N? 560 is lucky enough to ever have ?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.20,1:15:31.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,? 你是我们的兄弟 ?\N? You're our boy ?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.04,1:15:34.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,? 托尼・普罗 ?\N? Tony Pro ?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.25,1:15:39.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,? 我们都是你的兄弟 ?\N? We're all yours ?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.80,1:15:42.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,矮子就是托尼・普罗文扎诺\NThe Little Guy was Tony Provenzano.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.79,1:15:44.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人称托尼・普罗\NThey called him Tony Pro.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.12,1:15:47.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是新泽西一个大帮派的首领\NHe was a capo in a big Jersey crew
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.62,1:15:50.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并且是新泽西联合市\Nand the president of the Local 560
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.33,1:15:52.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,560号地方工会的主席\Nin Union City, New Jersey.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.80,1:16:06.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,? 他是最伟大的人 ?\N? He's the greatest guy ?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.37,1:16:12.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,? 能有他是560号地方工会之幸 ?\N? 560 is lucky enough to ever have ?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.70,1:16:14.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,托尼  托尼  托尼\NTony! Tony! Tony!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.62,1:16:17.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,托尼  托尼  托尼\NTony! Tony! Tony!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.87,1:16:21.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,普罗和吉米  他们一起发迹\NPro and Jimmy, they came up together
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.95,1:16:24.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们曾经很亲近\Nand they were close... for a while.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.83,1:16:27.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们没日没夜地工作\NYou turl, you work,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.75,1:16:30.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而大企业的老板们\Nwhile the corporation kings
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.33,1:16:32.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,行业的骄子们\Nand princes of industry,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.45,1:16:34.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们坐拥巨额报销账单\Nwith their vast expense accounts
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.50,1:16:37.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,高昂薪水  以及豪华游艇\Nand salary and luxurous yachts,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.16,1:16:40.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,却致力于毁灭我们\Nhave dedicated themselves to our destruction.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.66,1:16:41.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,打倒他们\NDown on them!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.79,1:16:46.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我用不着谁来跟我说托尼・普罗的故事\NI didn't need nobody to tell me about Tony Pro.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.79,1:16:49.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我还需要知道些什么  我知道的够多了\NOh, no. What did I need to know? I knew enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.12,1:16:59.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这家伙让萨利・巴格斯\NThis is a man who had Sally Bugs strangle
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.20,1:17:01.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,勒死了"三指"托尼・卡斯特里图\NTony "Three Fingers" Castellito
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.04,1:17:04.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就因为三指在工会里的地位越来越高\Njust because Three Fingers was coming up big in the union.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.75,1:17:07.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那还是他自己人  那可是他自己人\NAnd it was his own guy. It was his own guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.62,1:17:17.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,萨尔瓦多・布里古里欧  绰号"小虫萨利"\N1979年脸中三枪身亡
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.70,1:17:26.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,托尼・普罗太担心\NTony Pro was so fucking worried
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.58,1:17:28.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这家伙会击败他\Nthat this guy was gonna beat him out
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.12,1:17:30.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以至于在让小虫萨利勒死他之后\Nthat after he had Sally Bugs strangle the guy,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.83,1:17:33.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还让萨利把他塞进了碎树机\Nhe had Sally stick him in a fucking tree shredder.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.79,1:17:35.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这样就再也没有竞争了\NThat way there'd be no competition,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.58,1:17:36.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,毕竟他已经粉身碎骨了\Nnot even from the grave.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.79,1:17:37.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他已经失控了\NHe's out of control.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.87,1:17:40.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拿这种人该怎么办\NWhat are you gonna do with a person like this?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.45,1:17:43.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他想从每个人那都分杯羹\NHe's got a hand in everybody's pocket.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.50,1:17:45.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,勒索货运公司\NShaking down the trucking companies.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.12,1:17:46.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你能想象吗\NCan you imagine that?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.41,1:17:47.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,四处威胁人\NThreatening people.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.83,1:17:50.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,偶尔威胁威胁人\NI mean, you know, threatening people once in a while,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.37,1:17:51.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没问题  我能理解\Nokay, I understand.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.87,1:17:52.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但一直威胁人呢\NBut all the time?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.75,1:17:56.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,会让人注意到我们  你明白吗\NIt's drawing attention to us, you understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.00,1:17:59.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那样的家伙会毁了工会的声誉\NGuys like that give the unions a bad name.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.33,1:18:02.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,得做点什么了\NSomething's got to be done.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.50,1:18:05.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我说真的  得做点什么了\NI mean it. Something's gotta be done.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.66,1:18:08.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,托尼毕竟是托尼...\NTony being Tony, uh...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.50,1:18:11.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不好...不好弄  我们不能...\Nthat ain't... that ain't easy. We can't...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.75,1:18:13.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不是那个意思  我不是\NI don't mean that. I don't...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:13.41,1:18:14.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是那个意思\NNot... Not that.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.87,1:18:15.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只是\NYeah, I'm just...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.50,1:18:18.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只是想让劳工阶层\NI'm just saying get working guys
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.33,1:18:20.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那些熟悉工会的  卡车司机工会的正式成员\Nwho know the unions, card-carrying Teamsters,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.95,1:18:21.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就像你我这样的\Nlike you and me.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.75,1:18:23.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,开始竞选\NStart running,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.12,1:18:25.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,接管几个地方工会\Ntake over some of the locals.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.58,1:18:27.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你觉得呢\NWhat do you think?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.25,1:18:29.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-他不会喜欢的  -谁\N- He ain't gonna like that. - Who?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.87,1:18:31.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去他的  他算什么东西\NFuck him. Who the fuck is he?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.87,1:18:32.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,地痞流氓罢了\NHe's a gangster.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.37,1:18:35.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我领导着工会  我是主席\NI run the union, I'm the president.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.50,1:18:36.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的意思是\NSo, I mean...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.04,1:18:40.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我所需要的是一些懂事的家伙\NAll I need is some guys who know their ways around.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.04,1:18:42.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,知道怎么把控自己\NKnow how to handle themselves, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.12,1:18:43.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,仅此而已\NThat's all.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.91,1:18:46.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以我想让你去竞选\NThat's why I want you to run for president
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.37,1:18:49.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,326号地方工会的主席\Nof Local 326.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.83,1:18:53.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你就是我的家人  弗兰克\NYou're like family to me, Frank. You know.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.54,1:18:55.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你  艾琳\NYou, Irene,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.41,1:18:57.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,孩子们\Nthe girls.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.62,1:18:58.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可爱的佩琪\NThe lovely Peggy.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.62,1:19:01.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但这并不是我这么做的原因\NBut that's not why I'm doing this.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.91,1:19:04.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我给你的一切都是你自己赢得的\NI'm not giving you anything you didn't earn,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.08,1:19:06.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都是你应得的\Nyou didn't deserve.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.91,1:19:08.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你觉得呢\NWhat do you think?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.66,1:19:13.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道该说什么了  吉米\NI...I don't know what to say, Jimmy.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.95,1:19:15.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我是说...  -只管说你愿意就好\N- I mean, um... - Well, just say you'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.04,1:19:18.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你只需要说愿意\NThat's all you got to say.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.08,1:19:20.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且  我能保证你会赢\NPlus, I can guarantee you're gonna win.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.45,1:19:23.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你只要竞选326号地方工会的主席\NHa! When you run for president
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.04,1:19:27.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你就一定会赢\Nof 326, you're gonna win.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.83,1:19:29.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我保证\NI guarantee it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.70,1:19:32.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好  没问题  我愿意\NYeah, okay, I'll do it. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.79,1:19:35.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,认真的吗\NYou mean it, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.70,1:19:37.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然  我很荣幸\NYeah, yeah. I'm... I'm honored.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.16,1:19:41.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我爱你  我真的爱你  抱一个\NI love you. I just love you, you know. Come here.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.04,1:19:42.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我爱你  伙计\NI love you, man.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.66,1:19:43.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,爱到难以言表\NI can't tell ya.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.87,1:19:45.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天\NOh, gee.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.08,1:19:46.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太好了\NThis is so good, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.25,1:19:48.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我终于能喘口气了\NI feel like I can breathe again.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.16,1:19:50.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太有意思了\NIt's so funny. I...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.83,1:19:51.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不知怎么地  我...\NSomehow I...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.16,1:19:55.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也不知道  我以为你会拒绝\NI don't know. I thought you would've said no.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.20,1:19:58.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很高兴你答应了\NI'm glad you said yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.50,1:20:00.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想说\NI mean...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.33,1:20:02.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弗兰克\NFrank...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:04.33,1:20:07.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你从来不显露情绪  很难判断\NYou never reveal how you feel, you know. It's hard to tell.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.91,1:20:09.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很荣幸  吉米  我不知道\NI'm honored, Jimmy. I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.62,1:20:11.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只是不知道该说什么\NIt's just I don't know what to... say,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.54,1:20:13.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是我很荣幸\Nyou know, but I'm honored.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.29,1:20:15.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就好\NWell, that's good.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.33,1:20:18.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让我感觉很好\NThat makes me feel good.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.28,1:20:21.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我能喘口气了\NI can breathe.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.75,1:20:23.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太好了\NThat's so great.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.87,1:20:26.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我\NI...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.20,1:20:54.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,卡车司机326号地方工会
Dialogue: 0,1:20:55.37,1:20:58.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我还能说什么  我的一切都是吉米给的\NWhat can I say? I mean, I owe it all to Jimmy.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.50,1:21:01.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他把我从运肉卡车中解救出来  给了我新的开始\NHe took me out of a meat truck, he gave me my start.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.75,1:21:05.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他给我了首个职位  他给了我第一个工会\NHe gave me my first charter. He gave me my first union.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.58,1:21:07.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你好  -你好\N- How are ya? - Hey, how are you?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.16,1:21:10.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是弗兰克・希兰  326号地方工会的新任主席\NFrank Sheeran, the new president of Union 326.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.00,1:21:13.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我来自我介绍一下  -很高兴认识你\N- I wanted to introduce myself. - Nice to meet ya.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.66,1:21:15.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你叫什么  -我叫阿尔\N- What's your name? - My name's Al.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.29,1:21:16.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阿尔  很高兴认识你\NAl. Nice to meet ya, Al.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.25,1:21:19.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-一点心意  -不  不用\N- A little something... - No, no. Don't need it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.66,1:21:20.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-确定吗  -当然\N- Sure? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.75,1:21:22.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只是过来问个好  自我介绍一下\NJust came here to say hello, introduce myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.54,1:21:24.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有什么需要  只管联系我  好吗\NYou need anything, just get in touch with me. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.75,1:21:25.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-你确定吗  -当然\N- You sure? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.79,1:21:26.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.70,1:21:28.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,弗兰克・希兰  326号地方工会主席
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.75,1:21:28.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以  我们假设  如果他们能证明\NSo, hypothetically, if they can prove
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.66,1:21:29.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你从他们那偷了东西\Nthat you stole from them,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.66,1:21:32.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们会想要你供出同伙的名字\Nwhat they're gonna want are names, so...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.33,1:21:37.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你愿意交代几个名字  免去牢狱之灾吗\NWould you be willing to give up names to keep from going to jail?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.37,1:21:39.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.50,1:21:41.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那你就没什么好担心的了\NOkay. So you got nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.75,1:21:44.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-律师会帮你摆平的  -谢谢  希兰先生\N- The lawyers will take care of it. - Thank you, Mr. Sheeran.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.41,1:21:58.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沿80号州际公路西段开过宾州\NThe Interstate 80 West through the rest of Pennsylvania,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.95,1:22:02.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后我们横穿俄亥俄州到托莱多\Nand then we'd go across Ohio all the way to Toledo,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.08,1:22:07.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,接着我们沿着75号公路北上底特律\Nand then we'd go 75 North to Detroit.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.91,1:22:10.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,依然能够准时到达\NAnd we'd still get there on time.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.00,1:22:15.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,法官阁下  法律顾问已经告诉我的委托人\NYour Honor, my client had been advised by counsel
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.37,1:22:17.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她妻子作为货运公司所有者之一\Nthat it was perfectly legal for his wife
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.58,1:22:19.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是完全合法的\Nto be part owner of a trucking business.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.91,1:22:23.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而在麦克莱伦委员会质询其合法性时\NStill, when the McClellan Committee challenged its legality,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.91,1:22:23.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,美国参议院针对工人\N及管理层不当行为特别委员会
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.04,1:22:24.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她第一时间退出了公司\Nshe withdrew from the company immediately.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:25.45,1:22:27.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,事情到此就该告一段落\NThat should be the end of the matter.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:28.25,1:22:30.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在十三次大陪审团调查中\NThere had been not one indictment served
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.45,1:22:33.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的委托人没有一次被判有罪\Nagainst my client in 13 grand jury investigations.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.62,1:22:37.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,法官阁下  这是典型的\NYour Honor, this is an example of
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.50,1:22:39.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对我的委托人和他的家人的恶意报复\Na personal vendetta against my client,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.79,1:22:43.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是令人失望的司法部和司法部长罗伯特・肯尼迪\Nagainst his family, by a frustrated Justice Department
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.45,1:22:45.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在针对我的委托人\Nand the attorney general, Robert Kennedy.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:52.45,1:22:53.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他手上有枪\NHe's got a gun!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.62,1:23:00.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把枪先抢下来\NGet that gun out of his hand!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.04,1:23:04.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别激动  小伙子\NEasy, boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.87,1:23:12.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那不是真枪吧\NThat was not a real gun, was it?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.58,1:23:13.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,枪是怎么进来的\NHow'd that gun get in?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.08,1:23:15.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么进来的\NHow'd it get in here?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:15.16,1:23:16.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,又不是我的错\NIt wasn't my fault!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.87,1:23:17.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也不知道\NI don't know!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.30,1:23:19.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的查奇\NMy Chuckie!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.79,1:23:21.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是我儿子\NHey, it's my son!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.70,1:23:23.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是我的孩子  我把他养大的\NThat's my kid. I raised this kid.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.83,1:23:25.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们看见了吗  看见他的英勇之举了吗\NYou see him? You see what he did?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.33,1:23:29.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我告诉你们\NI'll tell you this.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.50,1:23:32.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他冲我开了枪  感觉像是小弹丸似的\NHe shot at me, and it was like a pellet or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.58,1:23:34.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没什么感觉  就一点点冲击力\NI didn't feel it, I just felt a little impact,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.70,1:23:36.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,甚至还比不上被BB枪打了\Nlike I was shot not even with a BB gun.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.00,1:23:38.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,比BB枪更弱\NSomething even lighter.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.87,1:23:39.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我冲向了他\NBut I charged him.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.12,1:23:42.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我和查奇都冲向了他  如果你们看见了的话\NI charged him and so did Chuckie, if you noticed.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.16,1:23:43.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我把他教得很好\NI taught him well.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.41,1:23:46.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,遇到持枪的永远要冲上去\NYou charge a guy, always charge a guy with a gun.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.29,1:23:48.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果是持刀的跑就行了\NWith a knife, you run away.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.00,1:23:51.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,遇到持刀的就跑  持枪的就冲\NRun away from a knife. So you charge with a gun,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.20,1:23:53.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-持刀的就跑  -没错\N- with a knife, you run. - That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.33,1:23:55.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我还押韵了\NHey! I rhymed!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.41,1:23:59.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道很难让人相信  但我收到了上头的消息\NI know it sounds crazy, but I got a message from a higher power
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.08,1:24:02.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,田纳西州纳什维尔警局
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.87,1:24:01.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让我杀了吉米・霍法\Ntelling me to shoot Jimmy Hoffa.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.41,1:24:02.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跟我来\NCome with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.16,1:24:04.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,纳什维尔有很多疯子  弗兰克\NA lot of nuts in Nashville, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.29,1:24:06.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,快过来  弗兰克\NCome on down, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.12,1:24:08.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在我边上就有一个\NYeah, I got one of them with me now, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.16,1:24:09.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,快过来  弗兰克\NGet down here, Frank.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:09.33,1:24:11.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾迪・帕丁  巴顿鲁日的那家伙\NEddie Partin, you know the guy from Baton Rouge,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.45,1:24:12.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他也在这里\Nhe's here with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.50,1:24:13.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好  我马上过去\NYeah. Yeah, I'll get right down.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.83,1:24:15.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别挡道  伙计们  让让\NOut of my way, boys. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:16.95,1:24:17.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让让\NCome on, come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.25,1:24:24.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,布伦南先生是否先说了\NDid Mr. Brennan first say,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.91,1:24:26.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或者你是否记得他首先说了\Nor do you remember him first saying
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.58,1:24:29.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,像是"我要更改交易条款\Nsomething about, say, "I had to change the deal.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.58,1:24:31.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我得让霍法也分一杯羹"这样的话\NI have to cut Hoffa in on the new deal"?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.70,1:24:34.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这不就是整件事的源头吗\NWasn't that like the chronology of the whole thing?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.87,1:24:37.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道他变更了交易条款\NI don't know he changed the deal,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.08,1:24:40.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我在电话这头的理解是\Nbut it was my understanding over the telephone that Brennan
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.62,1:24:41.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,布伦南只代表了他自己\Nwas speaking for himself.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.87,1:24:44.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她看上去很愤怒  这一看就很愤怒\NShe's an angry woman. That's an angry woman.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.45,1:24:44.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是啊\NOh. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.04,1:24:47.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我想她曾经是个老师  -没错\N- She was a teacher I think. - Oh, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.25,1:24:48.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们现在研究的是这个\NWhat we're looking at is this one.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.91,1:24:50.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个可不好搞定\NThis one is not approachable.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.20,1:24:51.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她很难攻破\NNo, she'd be a tough nut to crack.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.91,1:24:53.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有很多家族财产\NThere's a lot of family money there.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.50,1:24:55.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...将会截停搜查\N...will hail, stop, and search
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.20,1:24:56.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所有驶往古巴的船只\Nall ships bound for Cuba.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:57.04,1:24:59.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,若船长不停船\NIf the ships' captains do not stop,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.04,1:25:00.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们将采取武力截停\Nforce will be used to stop them.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.95,1:25:02.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果船停下...\NIf the ships do stop...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.25,1:25:04.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得可以选这个\NSee, I think there's an in here...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.50,1:25:05.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是否对大陪审团\NDid you make this statement
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.25,1:25:07.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,做出过如下陈述\Nto the grand jury? I'll read it for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.50,1:25:08.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"布伦南过来跟我说了些\N"Brennan came to me and said words
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.00,1:25:10.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,类似于他要继续的话..."\Nto the effect he's gonna go ahead..."
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.70,1:25:11.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他开了家餐厅\NHe's got a restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.00,1:25:13.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你查过违法行为了吗\NDid you look into violations?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.25,1:25:15.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,查了  我更愿意选女人\NYeah. I'd rather stick with the women.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.12,1:25:16.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-她们更好搞定  -吉米  谢谢\N- They're more approachable. - Jimmy, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.33,1:25:20.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...已在古巴部署可用的中程导弹\N...in Cuba of operational medium-range missiles.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.25,1:25:22.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他还表示如果导弹发射\NHe added that if one of the missiles is launched,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.75,1:25:25.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可能会携带有核弹头\Nit would probably carry a nuclear warhead.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.41,1:25:28.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,能够打击美国东南部任何地区\NIt could hit any spot in the southeast United States,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.41,1:25:29.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以及华盛顿南部\Nsouth of Washington.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.87,1:25:32.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而我们无法拦截\NAnd that we would have no way of intercepting it
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.33,1:25:34.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也无法提前预警\Nor issuing a warning about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.50,1:25:36.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这位嫁给了一个叫普莱切特的州警\NThis one's married to a state trooper named Plechette.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.70,1:25:38.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不错\NThat's good.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.62,1:25:40.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有门路吗\NWe know anyone?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.58,1:25:43.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有  地方工会有个当过警察的\NWell, yeah, we got an ex-cop in the Local.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.04,1:25:44.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很好\NThat's good.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.12,1:25:48.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的所有部队都提高了警戒级别\NAll our forces have been put on increased alert.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.58,1:26:11.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,过来跟我聊了几句  大意是\N...came to me and said words to the effect
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.41,1:26:14.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他打算开家公司出租卡车\Nhe's gonna go ahead and set up a company to lease trucks.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.37,1:26:17.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但之后  他又打电话  他的原话是\NBut later, he called me on the phone and said quote,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.25,1:26:18.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"我要更改交易条款\N"I gotta change the deal
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.87,1:26:21.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为我要让霍法也分一杯羹"\N'cause I gotta cut Hoffa in on the deal."
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.62,1:26:22.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是这样吗  先生\NIs that accurate, sir?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.00,1:26:24.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是另一个可以下手的对象\NThis one's another possibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.00,1:26:26.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-等等  -她有过情人\N- Wait. - Well, she had a boyfriend,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:26.83,1:26:28.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她婚后还跟别人有一腿\Nshe's seeing somebody else while she's married.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.12,1:26:31.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以可以用这个要挟她\NSo it could be... It could grab her,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.62,1:26:32.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-抓着她不放  -对  但是...\N- hold on to her. - Yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.58,1:26:33.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但这家伙\NBut this guy,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.70,1:26:36.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,开建筑公司的  做过一些违反的事情\Nthe construction business. He has a couple of violations,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.25,1:26:39.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他的房子有留置权\Nthere's a lien on his house.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.58,1:26:40.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,车还没付钱\NHis car is unpaid.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.75,1:26:44.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很好  继续  别在领先的时候放弃\NThat's good. Keep going. Don't quit while you're ahead.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.75,1:26:54.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢  回见  大艾迪\NThank you. See you, Big Eddie.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.16,1:26:55.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是否向上帝发誓\NDo you swear to tell the truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.25,1:26:56.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你所说的全是事实\Nthe whole truth and nothing but the truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.83,1:26:58.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-没有任何隐瞒  -我发誓\N- so help you God? - I do.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.75,1:27:09.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,金先生  你是\NMr. King, you're a member of
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.37,1:27:12.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,国际卡车司机工会的成员  对吗  先生\Nthe International Brotherhood of Teamsters, is that correct, sir?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.75,1:27:16.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,恕我拒绝回答这个问题\NI respectfully decline to answer that under the
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.41,1:27:20.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要行使第五修正案赋予我的权利\Nprotection afforded me by the Fifth Amendment.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.25,1:27:21.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只是问你是不是卡车司机工会的  先生\NI just asked if you're a Teamster, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.00,1:27:23.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,恕我拒绝回答...\NI respectfully decline to answer...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.37,1:27:25.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好  没问题  行\NOkay. All right. Fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.75,1:27:27.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要给你看张照片  行吗\NI'm gonna show you a photograph, all right?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.66,1:27:30.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-恕我拒绝回答....  -等等\N- I respectfully decline to answer... - Wait. Wait. Wait. Wait...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.04,1:27:31.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要行使...\N...under the protection...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:31.29,1:27:36.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,田纳西州警
Dialogue: 0,1:27:31.87,1:27:33.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你还没看这张照片\NYou haven't even seen the photograph yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:33.54,1:27:35.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看着这张照片  好好看看\NLook at the photograph, wait a smidge,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:35.58,1:27:38.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-然后你可以...  -根据我的理解\N- and then you can... - I want to avail myself
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.70,1:27:42.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想援引宪法赋予我的权利\Nof my right under the constitution, as I understand it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.79,1:27:44.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,威廉・E・米勒法官阁下
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.75,1:27:46.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-吉米  让他援引自己的权利  -好吧\N- Jim, let him avail himself. - Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.75,1:27:53.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,希尔德布兰特糖果冰淇淋店
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.58,1:27:54.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是啊\NOh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.08,1:27:56.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,金是最棒的\NThat King's the best.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.16,1:27:58.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是最棒的  他是个好人\NHe's the best. He's a good guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.54,1:28:01.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你看到他是怎样对付那个混蛋的吗\NYou see him stand up to that jerk?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.08,1:28:02.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看到了  看到了  我知道  他很棒\NYeah, yeah, I know. He was great.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.04,1:28:04.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就喜欢他这么干\NI love what he did.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.16,1:28:06.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们想让他开口  他们尽了全力\NThey tried to get him, they tried their best.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.08,1:28:08.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我们需要更多他这样的人  -天啊\N- We need more like him. - Oh, my God!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:10.29,1:28:11.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们刚刚收到更多详细信息\NMore details just arrived.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.70,1:28:16.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些详细信息是最新的\NThese details are not the same as previously.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:16.41,1:28:17.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,肯尼迪总统在车队\NPresident Kennedy, shot today,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.00,1:28:20.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,离开达拉斯市区时遇刺\Njust as his motorcade left downtown Dallas.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.79,1:28:21.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,肯尼迪夫人上前\NMrs. Kennedy jumped up
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.00,1:28:25.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱住肯尼迪先生  大喊"不"\Nand grabbed Mr. Kennedy. She called, "Oh, no!"
Dialogue: 0,1:28:25.04,1:28:26.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,车队加速驶离\NThe motorcade sped on.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.66,1:28:30.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,合众社报道称肯尼迪总统受的\NUnited Press says that the wounds of President Kennedy
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.83,1:28:33.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可能是致命伤\Nperhaps could be fatal.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.79,1:28:36.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,正在重播哥伦比亚广播公司新闻发出的简报\NRepeating a bulletin from CBS News.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:36.83,1:28:38.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,肯尼迪总统在得克萨斯州的达拉斯市\NPresident Kennedy has been shot
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.04,1:28:42.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,被一名嫌疑刺客开枪击中\Nby a would-be assassin in Dallas, Texas.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:42.37,1:28:44.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请继续关注哥伦比亚广播公司新闻\NStay tuned to CBS News for
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.47,1:28:45.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,了解更多详细信息\Nfurther details.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.95,1:28:46.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.75,1:28:51.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要做出一杯真正的咖啡\NIt takes more than an instant
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.83,1:28:53.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一瞬间可不够\Nto make a real cup of coffee.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.12,1:28:57.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因此雀巢咖啡研制出了一种新产品\NThat's why Nescafé has come up with a new kind of coffee.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:57.95,1:29:02.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这不只是一种即溶咖啡  而是新的雀巢分钟煮咖啡\NIt's more than an instant. It's new Minute Brew Nescafé.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.66,1:29:03.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人人都能做出...\NAnybody can make a...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:03.75,1:29:05.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这显然是一则官方简报\NThe flash, apparently official,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.00,1:29:11.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,肯尼迪总统于中部标准时间下午一点\NPresident Kennedy died at 1:00 p.m. Central standard time,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.66,1:29:14.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,东部标准时间下午两点去世\Ntwo o'clock, eastern standard time,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.50,1:29:16.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大约38分钟前\Nsome 38 minutes ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.12,1:29:26.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,副总统约翰逊已离开位于达拉斯的医院\NVice President Johnson has left the hospital in Dallas,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.45,1:29:29.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我们不知道他将前往哪里\Nbut we do not know, uh, to where he has proceeded.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.25,1:29:33.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,预计他很快将宣誓就职\NPresumably, he will be taking the oath of office shortly
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.04,1:29:38.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,成为第36届美国总统\Nand become the 36th President of the United States.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.83,1:29:48.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,国际卡车司机工会
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.08,1:29:46.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,霍法先生  你会参加\NMr. Hoffa, will you be attending
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.45,1:29:47.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,总统的葬礼吗\Nthe President's funeral?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.12,1:29:49.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没有受邀\NI wasn't invited.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.20,1:29:51.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不一定要受邀  上百万的美国人都会参加\NYou don't have to be invited. A million Americans will be there.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.04,1:29:52.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那...\NWell...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.45,1:29:55.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想我得查查我的日程\NI guess I'll have to check my schedule.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.20,1:29:57.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你去参加并被请求发言  你会说什么\NIf you were to go and asked to speak, what would you say?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.12,1:29:59.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会说\NI'd say, uh,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.87,1:30:02.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,鲍比・肯尼迪现在只是个普通律师了\NBobby Kennedy is just another lawyer now.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.79,1:30:08.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,混蛋\NSon of a bitch.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.12,1:30:11.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,国际卡车司机工会
Dialogue: 0,1:30:24.20,1:30:25.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很好  埃里克  非常感谢\NGood, Eric. Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.91,1:30:37.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,吉米说得对\NJimmy was right.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.95,1:30:39.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,几乎是对的\NAlmost.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.70,1:30:43.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,鲍比的刁难到此为止了\NThat was the end of it with Bobby.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:44.62,1:30:47.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他卸任司法部长了  事情了结了\NSo much for him being the attorney general. That was done.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.00,1:30:53.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,鲍比跟我们的宿怨结束了\NBobby's vendetta was over, with us.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:59.83,1:31:00.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,霍法先生\NMr. Hoffa,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.91,1:31:03.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你因损害了这个国家的灵魂\Nyou stand here convicted of having tampered
Dialogue: 0,1:31:03.91,1:31:05.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,被判有罪\Nwith the very soul of this nation.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.83,1:31:09.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但纳什维尔那个陪审团的事情还没完\NBut there was still that jury thing in Nashville.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.08,1:31:11.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先生  这个国家的灵魂在于\NThe soul of this nation, sir,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.37,1:31:14.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它神圣的司法程序\Nlies in its sacred processes of justice.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.62,1:31:16.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,正义必须得到伸张\NJustice must be done.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:17.58,1:31:20.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你因为曾邪恶地企图破坏这套程序\NAnd for your wicked attempts to corrupt these processes,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.16,1:31:23.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,将会受到法律的制裁\Njustice will be done on you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:25.25,1:31:26.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们终于抓到他了\NWe got him now.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.95,1:31:28.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们抓到他了\NWe got him.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.04,1:31:31.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,女士们先生们  我们做到了\NLadies and gentlemen, we did it!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.25,1:31:37.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,囚车不作鸣枪警示
Dialogue: 0,1:31:48.54,1:31:51.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是吉米把一切都安排妥当了\NBut Jimmy, you know, he had it all set up.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.54,1:31:54.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,虽然表面看起来是\NAlthough you knew it was supposed to look like Fitz
Dialogue: 0,1:31:54.75,1:31:56.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,菲茨在管事\Nwas the one in charge.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.66,1:31:58.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但他通过比尔・巴法利诺和\NHe gave Fitz his orders through
Dialogue: 0,1:31:58.20,1:32:01.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,詹姆斯・R・霍法
Dialogue: 0,1:31:58.27,1:31:59.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,艾伦・多夫曼给菲茨下指令\NBill Bufalino and Allen Dorfman,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.00,1:32:01.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们还替吉米放贷\Nand they ran Jimmy's loans.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.79,1:32:03.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在里面待得还好吗  一切都...\NBut things are good in here? Everything is...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.96,1:32:04.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一切都糟透了\NEverything's terrible.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.79,1:32:06.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,夜不能寐  因为担心\NYou don't sleep at night 'cause you're afraid
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.70,1:32:08.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有人会拿刀捅你\Nsomeone's gonna knife you.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:08.79,1:32:10.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但你看上去不错  还不错\N'Cause you look okay. You look okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.20,1:32:12.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,菲茨在哪  他迟到了\NWhere's Fitz? He's late.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.12,1:32:15.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们本来要在正门等他的  他...\NYeah. Well, we were gonna meet him in the front. He...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.70,1:32:16.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在正门等他吗\NMeet him in the front?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.83,1:32:17.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他来了  他来了\NHere he is, here he is.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:17.79,1:32:20.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你到底去哪了  你来这干什么\NWhere the hell have you been? What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.37,1:32:22.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你到底来干什么  菲茨\NWhy did you even come at all, Fitz?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.66,1:32:23.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道自己迟到了吗\NYou know, are you aware you're late?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:23.91,1:32:25.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就想知道这个  你知道自己迟到了吗\NThat's all I want to know. Do you know you're late?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.50,1:32:26.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对不起我迟到了  吉米\NI'm sorry I'm late, Jimmy,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.25,1:32:27.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我们有很多事要做\Nbut we got a lot going on.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:27.87,1:32:28.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们有很多事要做\NWe got a lot going on.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.83,1:32:31.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不想听这种话  我想听点具体的\NI don't wanna hear that. I wanna hear something concrete,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.54,1:32:33.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想听你直入正题\NI wanna hear something straight on.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.16,1:32:36.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只想请你耐心一点\NI'm just gonna ask you to be a little more patient.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:36.37,1:32:37.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得我们会...\NI think we're gonna have...
